export async function queryView(read: ReadStore, recipientId: string): Promise<InboxView | null> {
  return read.load(recipientId);
}
```

The write side computes events from an aggregate state; the read side answers queries from a projection. The two sides share the event DU but never the state type -- the read view is shaped for lookup, not invariants.

